---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { org, socials } from '../data/site';
---
<Base title="About | Blue Leaf Labs" description="Blue Leaf Labs is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit linking engineering, climate science, and economics to turn research into practical change, founded and run by Rohan Agarwal.">
  <div class="wrap page-intro">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    <h1>About Blue Leaf Labs</h1>
    <p>
      Blue Leaf Labs is {org.legal}, founded and run by Rohan Agarwal. It exists to advance
      climate systems research and open scientific education, and to put that work to public use.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="prose serif" style="max-width:72ch">
        <figure class="fig headshot">
          <img src="/images/uploads/rohan-headshot.jpg" alt="Rohan Agarwal, founder of Blue Leaf Labs" />
        </figure>
        <p>
          I'm Rohan Agarwal, a researcher, teacher, and performer, and a dual-enrolled sophomore
          at Monta Vista High School and De Anza College in Cupertino, CA.
        </p>
        <p>
          I believe that true change happens only when engineering innovation becomes an economic
          driver. I founded Blue Leaf Labs to explore this space, focusing on energy, climate, and the
          use of insightful data to drive real-world action. My work is hands-on and transparent: I
          design prototypes, test them rigorously, and share my methods openly so others can build on
          what I've learned. Collaboration is integral to this process, and I enjoy working with fellow
          researchers, educators, and community groups to validate and share results.
        </p>

        <h2>Researcher</h2>
        <p>
          My current work searches for solutions to environmental challenges that are feasible from an
          engineering standpoint and drive economic self-interest:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Blue Energy:</strong> building and testing benchtop stacks for osmotic power (blue energy), with a focus on load-sweep instrumentation and real-world economic feasibility.</li>
          <li><strong>Decision Tools:</strong> turning messy data into clear, actionable insights through single-metric visualizations and lightweight dashboards.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Teacher</h2>
        <p>
          I'm passionate about making complex ideas accessible. My teaching with Dynamic Teaching for
          the City of Cupertino ranges from the school-year Advanced Topics in Mathematics to
          custom-crafted summer programs in environmental engineering and scientific inquiry. Working
          with students from fifth to twelfth grade, I invest a lot of time designing materials that
          bring abstract concepts to life with clear examples, cheat-sheets, and small tools they can use
          long after class ends. I'm currently designing an environmental awareness course for
          Summer 2026.
        </p>

        <h2>Performer</h2>
        <p>
          Outside of engineering, I'm a musician. I play Hindustani classical tabla and Western violin,
          and I've been singing for over a decade. My fascination with rhythm, signal, and structure in
          music often directly informs how I approach sensors and data in the lab. You can find some of
          my latest compositions on <a href={socials.instagram}>Instagram</a> and
          <a href={socials.youtube}>YouTube</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
